Fun fact about me: I used to be an esthetician so I’ve always been really into skincare. Something that’s always been a priority for me is finding brands that are vegan and use super clean ingredients which is why a huge majority of my skincare routine AND even @therealtarekelmoussa’s routine is filled with @fitglowbeauty products. 🙌 I’ve been using Fitglow for over 3 years now and honestly guys I can’t say enough good things. Yes, this is a sponsored post but this is a brand I love and truly think you guys can benefit from (otherwise I wouldn’t be posting them). 

And it’s cute because when I first started dating Tarek I realized he had literally 0 skincare routine so I changed that one up pretty fast and got him into Fitglow’s Cloud Ceramide Foam Cleanser and the Cloud Comfort Cream and now he doesn’t go a night without using them 😆

The products in this video are some of our holy grail products. We both have sensitive skin and we can breakout really easily but all of Fitglow’s products are super soothing and don’t irritate us at all so to anyone here who’s worried about that- this is 100% the brand for you. Had so much fun making this His & Hers skincare routine with a brand that we both genuinely love so much and please lmk in the comments below if you guys want to see more like this or if you have any questions about Fitglow’s products and use my code HEATHER30 for 30% off!! #leapingbunnycertified #veganskincare #ad #fitglowbeautyskincare

I know you guys have been waiting to see it!! A tour of our new beach home for the rest of the year! 
-

Earlier this year @therealtarekelmoussa & I sold his “dadchelor” pad. I represented him in the sale, we got multiple offers and it sold very quick. So we were left searching for a home quick. We found this summer beach house & fell in love with it. Making new memories together in our new home. 
-

Welcome to our home!!! Come on in and take a tour with us and @people @peopletv

node.text:
Photo dump from the most beautiful day. 🙏🏻🤍

Responded to a lot of your questions on stories today but a lot of you guys asked similar questions so I’ll use this to answer a few more ☺️: 

🤍 Q: When’s your wedding 
I’m not going to share the exact date just yet but all I’ll say is that it’s coming up soon and we can’t wait ☺️

🤍Q: How did you decide who to invite? 
I had the same mentality for both the bridal shower and the wedding- I wanted it to feel intimate. For the bridal shower I only invited my family and my closest friends and that was the best decision for me. The room was filled with so much love so I can’t imagine doing it any other way ☺️

🤍 Q: Who planned the bridal shower? 
I had some help from my amazing assistant and our amazing wedding planners @purelavishevents. Wedding planning and all the planning leading up to it is not my thing so wanted to leave it to the experts but to everyone who’s planning a bridal shower all I can say is that it doesn’t matter how big, small, extravagant, etc- all that matters is being with the people you love and celebrating your future marriage 🙏🏻

Those were the most asked questions but if you have any others ask them below and I’ll get to as many as I can 🥰

node.text: There’s something so special about having friends in your life who are like sisters to you. These girls have been through so much with me- the good and the bad- and I couldn’t love them more. These girls knew me back in the day when I had NOTHING, not even a couple dollars to my name, and when I would drive up to LA every day to hustle and work. They were with me when I was in my twenties and saw me striving to get to where I am today. I think a lot of people just assume I walked into this life and got everything handed to me but these girls know the real truth and have watched me put my all into my career and put my all into finding a love like what I have with @therealtarekelmoussa since day one. They’re my forever girls and I’m so lucky to have this kind of friendship in my life. 🤍🤍

node.text: Today was a special day. Today we celebrated my bridal shower amongst the animals and unveiled my @peta campaign: Say “I do” to vegan 🤍 If you know me, you know I’m a huge animal lover. You might also know that I’ve been vegan for 11 years now and while I don’t believe in pushing a lifestyle on others, I do believe in doing what you can for the animals and the environment. I felt so at home today at the @kindredspiritscarefarm - all of the animals there have been rescued and given a second chance at life and it melted my heart to see how happy they were and how much personality all of them had. I got a big kiss from Ted the goat (sorry @therealtarekelmoussa for cheating on you 😜), I got to belly rub on a pig, and I got to feed an alpaca !! Being vegan doesn’t just make me feel better health wise, it also makes me so happy knowing that I am doing what I can to protect the animals and to help the environment. Even making little changes here and there counts so keep that in mind and CHEERS to a beautiful bridal shower with all my friends, family, + animal friends, too ☺️🐷🐐🦙🤍

Of course the first thing I did was thank everyone for coming then say “can we drink now!?” 😆 

Still not over how beautiful, perfect, and filled with love this day was. I grew up thinking and fantasizing about my wedding and all the events leading up to it and all I can say is that not only has everything been better than I could’ve ever imagined, but the love I feel for my future husband is honestly the love I have been looking for my entire life. I am so blessed and CHEERS to my first and last bridal shower… but definitely not my last champagne tower 😉🥂🤍
